{"id":38078,"date":"2022-08-08T14:04:36","date_gmt":"2022-08-08T10:04:36","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=38078"},"modified":"2022-08-08T14:05:53","modified_gmt":"2022-08-08T10:05:53","slug":"as-if-to-say-farewell","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/08\/08\/as-if-to-say-farewell\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Sunnah: The Prophet speaks as if to say farewell"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn Amr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, came out to us one day as if to say farewell. The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>I am Muhammad, the unlettered prophet. There is no prophet after me. I have been given words that are eloquent, comprehensive, and decisive. I know how many angels guard the Hellfire and carry the Throne. Leniency came through me and I was pardoned along with my nation. Thus, listen and obey me as long as I am among you. When I am taken away, then you must adhere to the Book of Allah. Make lawful what it declares to be lawful and forbid what it declares to be forbidden.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 6981<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Ahmad Shakir<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064e\u0645\u0652\u0631\u0650\u0648 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0639\u064e\u0627\u0635\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u062e\u064e\u0631\u064e\u062c\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0645\u064b\u0627 \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0652\u064